Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.21,0:45:11.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他和朋友在一起  爸爸\N{\fs16\fsp0}He's with his friends! Dad!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.88,0:45:13.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不要把你爸爸扯进来\N{\fs16\fsp0}Leave him out of this. He's suffered enough.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:13.92,0:45:16.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他已经有六星期消化不良了\N{\fs16\fsp0}He hasn't digested a decent meal in six weeks.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.66,0:45:29.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你去了些什么地方  为什么不打电话\N{\fs16\fsp0}Where were you? Why didn't you call?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.00,0:45:34.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们担心死了  已婚男人不该整夜不归\N{\fs16\fsp0}We were worried to death. A married man does not stay out like this.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:36.67,0:45:39.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,正常人没有这种行为的\N{\fs16\fsp0}Normal people don't act like this!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:40.78,0:45:42.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你哪里不对劲\N{\fs16\fsp0}What's wrong with you?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:42.98,0:45:46.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她没说错  你是不正常  你哪里不对劲\N{\fs16\fsp0}You're not normal. She's right. What's wrong with you?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:46.98,0:45:50.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你有什么毛病  你是什么样的人\N{\fs16\fsp0}What kind of person are you? What is the matter with you?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:50.75,0:45:52.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们那些家伙是哪种人\N{\fs16\fsp0}What kind of people are they?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.69,0:45:58.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们嫁的不是上班族\N{\fs16\fsp0}We weren't married to nine-to-five guys.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:58.49,0:46:01.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,让我感到有多不同\N{\fs16\fsp0}But the first time I realized how different...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.43,0:46:03.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是在美琪的家庭聚会时\N{\fs16\fsp0}was when Mickey had a hostess party.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.53,0:46:07.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 凯伦  你是哪里人  - 劳伦斯\N{\fs16\fsp0}- Karen, where you from? - Lawrence.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.30,0:46:11.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在长岛  不错呀  我生在迈阿密  你去过吗\N{\fs16\fsp0}On the Island. It's nice. I'm from Miami. You ever been there?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:12.01,0:46:15.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那里还不错  像个犹太天堂\N{\fs16\fsp0}It's okay, but it's like you died and woke up in Jew heaven.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:16.34,0:46:18.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不要老挤痘子嘛\N{\fs16\fsp0}Angie, stop picking at that thing.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:18.51,0:46:19.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我真想揍他的脸\N{\fs16\fsp0}I'd like to smack his face.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.05,0:46:21.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那个红发男人\N{\fs16\fsp0}The red-haired guy, looks like a farmer?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:21.82,0:46:23.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他都要动手动脚的\N{\fs16\fsp0}The guy's hands are all over me.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:24.02,0:46:28.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我说  不要对我动手  否则我把它切下来\N{\fs16\fsp0}So I told him, "Keep your fucking hands off me, or I'll cut them off."{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:29.99,0:46:31.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她是认真的\N{\fs16\fsp0}She means it.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:31.56,0:46:34.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他不知道多走运  如果我告诉韦力\N{\fs16\fsp0}You don't know how lucky he is. I just mention this to Vinnie...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:35.40,0:46:38.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你怎么能告诉韦力  他非杀了他不可\N{\fs16\fsp0}How can you mention it? Vinnie would kill him.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.70,0:46:42.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,说出来  韦力杀了他  又得去坐一辈子牢\N{\fs16\fsp0}If I don't, he'll kill the miserable bastard, then Vinnie will be there for life.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:42.74,0:46:45.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你以为只有你有麻烦呀  珍妮的儿子更糟\N{\fs16\fsp0}You think you got problems. What about Jeannie's kid?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.54,0:46:49.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在一场只有10元输赢的扑克中和人争执起来  他拿出枪\N{\fs16\fsp0}He was in an argument. A $10 card game. He pulls out a gun.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:49.44,0:46:53.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,枪走火  打死一个男孩  当他祖母听到他在牢里\N{\fs16\fsp0}The gun goes off. Some kid gets killed. When the grandmother hears it...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.41,0:46:57.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,心脏病发作  当场就死了\N{\fs16\fsp0}and finds out he's jailed, she has a heart attack and drops dead right on the spot.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.52,0:47:01.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在珍妮的老公和孩子在牢里  妈妈在殡仪馆\N{\fs16\fsp0}Now Jeannie has a husband and son in jail and a mother in the funeral parlor.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:02.76,0:47:05.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 珍妮酗酒  - 也许她是心情不好\N{\fs16\fsp0}- Jeannie drinks. - Maybe she's depressed.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:05.69,0:47:07.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,饶了我吧  她根本就是酗酒\N{\fs16\fsp0}Give me a break. She's drunk.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:09.33,0:47:12.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只要有点事发生  他们都成圣人了\N{\fs16\fsp0}As soon as something happens, you make them out to be saints.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.83,0:47:17.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她们皮肤粗糙  化妆太浓  气色不好\N{\fs16\fsp0}They had bad skin and wore too much makeup. They didn't look very good.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.11,0:47:20.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她们看起来很憔悴  穿的衣服\N{\fs16\fsp0}They looked beat-up. And the stuff they wore...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.91,0:47:22.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也是不成套的廉价品\N{\fs16\fsp0}was thrown together and cheap.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.94,0:47:25.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,都是些裤装  针织品\N{\fs16\fsp0}A lot of pantsuits and double-knits.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:27.52,0:47:29.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她昼夜穿睡袍\N{\fs16\fsp0}She spends her life in a nightgown.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.42,0:47:31.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,相信我  她不是什么好东西\N{\fs16\fsp0}The woman is no angel, believe me.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:31.89,0:47:34.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她们谈论着她们的孩子多坏\N{\fs16\fsp0}They talked about their rotten kids...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.56,0:47:37.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她们用扫把揍孩子  她们用皮鞭揍孩子\N{\fs16\fsp0}and about beating them with broom handles and belts.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.29,0:47:40.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但孩子们一点也不理会\N{\fs16\fsp0}And that the kids still didn't pay any attention.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.39,0:47:42.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当亨利来接我的时候  我整个头都晕了\N{\fs16\fsp0}When Henry picked me up, I was dizzy.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.46,0:47:45.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不知道我能不能适应这种生活\N{\fs16\fsp0}I don't know if I could live like that.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:46.33,0:47:49.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你要是进了监牢  我怎么办\N{\fs16\fsp0}God forbid, what would happen if you had to go to prison?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:50.04,0:47:51.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,凯伦\N{\fs16\fsp0}Karen.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:52.04,0:47:54.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,美琪谈到了珍妮的丈夫\N{\fs16\fsp0}Mickey said that Jeannie's husband...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.21,0:47:56.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你知道怎么回事吗\N{\fs16\fsp0}Do you know why Jeannie's husband went to the can?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:56.64,0:48:00.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,珍妮的丈夫是为了逃避珍妮才去坐牢的\N{\fs16\fsp0}Because of Jeannie. He wanted to get away from her.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.18,0:48:04.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你听我说  坐牢的都是想坐牢的\N{\fs16\fsp0}Let me tell you something. Nobody goes to jail unless they want to.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:05.25,0:48:07.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,都是甘愿被捕的\N{\fs16\fsp0}Unless they make themselves get caught.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.35,0:48:09.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们没把事情安排好\N{\fs16\fsp0}They don't have things organized.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:09.29,0:48:12.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我都把事弄妥了\N{\fs16\fsp0}I know what I'm doing. I've got things organized with these guys.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:12.76,0:48:14.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你知道哪些人坐牢吗\N{\fs16\fsp0}You know who goes to jail?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.00,0:48:17.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,黑人抢劫犯  你知道他们为什么会被捕吗\N{\fs16\fsp0}Nigger stickup men. You know why they get caught?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:17.30,0:48:19.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为他们在逃走用的车上睡着了\N{\fs16\fsp0}Because they fall asleep in the getaway car, Karen.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:20.60,0:48:24.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,凯伦  不要瞎担心了  甜心  过来吧\N{\fs16\fsp0}Come on, don't worry so much, sweetie. Come here.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.73,0:48:33.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,渐渐地  一切都好像很正常了\N{\fs16\fsp0}After a while, it got to be all normal.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:34.20,0:48:36.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没有一样像犯罪\N{\fs16\fsp0}None of it seemed like crime.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:36.77,0:48:39.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,亨利就像在经营企业\N{\fs16\fsp0}It was more like Henry was enterprising...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.24,0:48:42.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他和伙伴以诈骗为生而已\N{\fs16\fsp0}and that he and the guys made bucks hustling while other guys...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:43.11,0:48:46.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,至少他们不坐着等别人来救济\N{\fs16\fsp0}were sitting on their asses waiting for handouts.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:46.92,0:48:50.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们的丈夫不是脑外科医生  他们是靠努力赚钱的\N{\fs16\fsp0}Our husbands weren't brain surgeons, they were blue-collar guys.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:51.05,0:48:55.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们只有多偷  多抢  才能多赚点钱\N{\fs16\fsp0}The only way they could make real extra money was to go out and cut corners.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.03,0:48:58.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,钱箱在那里  讨人厌的东西\N{\fs16\fsp0}Where's the strong box, you varmint?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.03,0:49:07.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你他妈的别动\N{\fs16\fsp0}Don't fucking move! Don't move.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:16.78,0:49:19.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 餐厅见了  - 我坐副驾驶座\N{\fs16\fsp0}- See you at the diner. - I'm riding shotgun.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:19.72,0:49:22.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你看他刚才立刻就服软了\N{\fs16\fsp0}Did you see him give it right over?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:22.55,0:49:25.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,走吧  回老巢去分钱吧\N{\fs16\fsp0}Back to the hideout to split up the loot.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:29.16,0:49:31.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们非常亲近\N{\fs16\fsp0}We were all so very close.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:31.63,0:49:35.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,从来不跟外人来往  绝不\N{\fs16\fsp0}There were never any outsiders around. Absolutely never.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:35.66,0:49:40.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就因为这样  一切好像更正常了\N{\fs16\fsp0}Being together all the time made everything seem all the more normal.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:40.50,0:49:41.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,哈罗  希尔太太  警察\N{\fs16\fsp0}Hello, Mrs. Hill. Police.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.00,0:49:46.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我是迪西警探  他是席维思警探  我们有搜查令\N{\fs16\fsp0}I'm Detective Deacy. This is Detective Silvestri. We have a search warrant.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:46.48,0:49:48.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,请看一下  然后签名\N{\fs16\fsp0}Would you read and sign it?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.74,0:49:50.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 哪里都行吗  - 是的\N{\fs16\fsp0}- Anywhere? - Yeah, anywhere.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:50.35,0:49:52.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,要耽误一点时间  我们每样都要仔细查\N{\fs16\fsp0}This'll take a while, we have to go through everything.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.08,0:49:56.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 你们要咖啡吗  - 不用了  谢谢你\N{\fs16\fsp0}- You boys want some coffee? - No coffee now, thanks.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.19,0:50:00.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 请当心点  - 我们只是照常执行任务\N{\fs16\fsp0}- Be careful. - We'll just go about our business.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.49,0:50:02.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,警察经常会找些小麻烦\N{\fs16\fsp0}There was always a little harassment.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.03,0:50:05.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们要跟亨利谈东谈西\N{\fs16\fsp0}They wanted to talk to Henry about this or that.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:05.99,0:50:09.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们带着传票和搜查令来叫我签名\N{\fs16\fsp0}They'd make me sign their subpoenas or warrants.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:09.40,0:50:11.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不论他们搜到什么\N{\fs16\fsp0}But mostly they just wanted a handout.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:11.93,0:50:15.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,几块钱也就把他们打发了\N{\fs16\fsp0}A few bucks to keep things quiet no matter what they found.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:20.58,0:50:25.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我每次都问他们  要不要咖啡  有的太太  像美琪\N{\fs16\fsp0}I always asked if they wanted coffee. Some wives, like Mickey Conway...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:25.71,0:50:28.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她总是诅咒他们  还吐口水在地板上\N{\fs16\fsp0}used to curse at them and spit on the floor.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:28.72,0:50:32.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我永远也不了解为什么要吐在自己的地板上\N{\fs16\fsp0}She used to spit on her own floor. That never made any sense to me.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:32.49,0:50:35.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还是礼貌一点  然后打电话给律师比较好\N{\fs16\fsp0}It was better to be polite and call the lawyer.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:44.63,0:50:49.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们总是在一起  总是同样一群人\N{\fs16\fsp0}We always did everything together, and we always were in the same crowd.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:49.30,0:50:53.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,纪念日  受洗等等  我们只到彼此的家去\N{\fs16\fsp0}Anniversaries, christenings. We only went to each other's houses.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:55.41,0:50:56.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,女士们一起玩牌\N{\fs16\fsp0}The women played cards.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:56.91,0:51:00.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,凡有婴儿诞生  美琪和吉米总是最先到医院的\N{\fs16\fsp0}When kids were born, Mickey and Jimmy were the first at the hospital.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:01.15,0:51:04.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当我们去南海或赌城度假\N{\fs16\fsp0}When we went to the Islands or Vegas for vacation...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:04.39,0:51:05.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也都是一起的\N{\fs16\fsp0}we went together.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:05.82,0:51:08.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,从来没有外人  好像那才是正常的\N{\fs16\fsp0}No outsiders ever. It got to be normal.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:09.02,0:51:12.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我甚至对我丈夫的所作所为\N{\fs16\fsp0}It got to where I was proud that I had the kind of husband...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:12.23,0:51:15.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,感到骄傲\N{\fs16\fsp0}who was willing to risk his neck just to get us the little extras.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:16.87,0:51:20.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我已经跟妈讲好了  明晚来替我们看孩子\N{\fs16\fsp0}But I got Mom to watch the babies tomorrow night.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.24,0:51:22.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 我没办法  凯伦  - 为什么\N{\fs16\fsp0}- Can't do it, Karen. - Why not?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:22.24,0:51:24.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就是不行嘛  我已安排好别的事了\N{\fs16\fsp0}I just can't. I got something lined up.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:25.37,0:51:28.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但妈妈只有明晚可以替我们看孩子\N{\fs16\fsp0}But tomorrow's the only night she can do it.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.71,0:51:32.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 拜托嘛  好不好  - 我真的不行  你要我怎么办\N{\fs16\fsp0}- Pretty please? - I can't. What do you want me to do?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:33.72,0:51:35.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 我得走了  - 等一下\N{\fs16\fsp0}- I got to go. - Wait a minute.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:37.02,0:51:39.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我要去逛街  给我点钱好吗\N{\fs16\fsp0}I wanted to go shopping. Can I get some money?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:39.49,0:51:41.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你需要多少\N{\fs16\fsp0}How much do you need?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:43.03,0:51:44.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 多少  - 这么多\N{\fs16\fsp0}- How much? - That much.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:49.70,0:51:52.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这么多  亲我一下\N{\fs16\fsp0}This much. Give me a kiss.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:56.14,0:51:57.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,待会见\N{\fs16\fsp0}See you later.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:02.85,0:52:04.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好吧\N{\fs16\fsp0}All right.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:12.69,0:52:20.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,纽约皇后区  1970年6月11日
Dialogue: 0,0:52:36.25,0:52:38.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,欢迎你回来\N{\fs16\fsp0}Welcome home, Batts.{\r}
