Dialogue: 0,0:59:25.82,0:59:29.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他老婆说  闭嘴  你话太多了\N{\fs16\fsp0}So she says, "Shut up! You're always talking."{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:31.03,0:59:33.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不过这句话用意大利语说出来好听多了\N{\fs16\fsp0}But in Italian, it sounds much nicer.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:33.70,0:59:35.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 自得其乐  - 就是 满于现况 的意思\N{\fs16\fsp0}- Cornuto contento. - That's it.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:35.40,0:59:39.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 什么意思呀  - 就是连那样他都满足\N{\fs16\fsp0}- What does that mean? - It means he's content to be a jerk.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:39.60,0:59:42.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,别人怎么想  他才不在乎\N{\fs16\fsp0}He doesn't care who knows it.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:42.50,0:59:45.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 汤米有没有告诉你们我画画  - 没有\N{\fs16\fsp0}- Did Tommy tell you about my painting? - No.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:46.11,0:59:47.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,看看这个\N{\fs16\fsp0}Look at this.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:47.91,0:59:49.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,真漂亮\N{\fs16\fsp0}It's beautiful.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:49.31,0:59:52.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一只狗脸朝这边  另一只脸朝那边\N{\fs16\fsp0}I like it. One dog goes one way and the other goes the other.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:52.51,0:59:54.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一只想到东部  一只想到西部  又怎样咧\N{\fs16\fsp0}One's facing east, the other west. So what?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:55.08,0:59:58.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这人在说  你要我怎么样  他那头白发挺漂亮的\N{\fs16\fsp0}He's saying, "What do you want from me?" The guy's got nice white hair.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:58.69,1:00:00.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,漂亮  那只狗  看起来差不多\N{\fs16\fsp0}Beautiful. The dog looks the same.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:01.02,1:00:03.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这个人有点像我们认识的一个人\N{\fs16\fsp0}Looks like somebody we know.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:04.76,1:00:06.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,去掉胡子不就是他吗\N{\fs16\fsp0}Without the beard. It's him.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:09.46,1:00:10.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就是他\N{\fs16\fsp0}It's him.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:20.24,1:00:21.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,妈的  什么声音啊\N{\fs16\fsp0}What the fuck is that?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:21.74,1:00:24.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对大部分兄弟来说  杀人是被接受的\N{\fs16\fsp0}For most of the guys, killings were accepted.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:24.51,1:00:27.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,要令每个人服从  只有用处决来控制\N{\fs16\fsp0}Murder was the only way everybody stayed in line.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:27.38,1:00:30.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你如果越轨就会被除掉  规则大家都知道\N{\fs16\fsp0}You got out of line, you got whacked. Everybody knew the rules.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:30.82,1:00:34.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有时候没越轨也会被除掉\N{\fs16\fsp0}Sometimes, even if people didn't get out of line, they got whacked.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:34.42,1:00:38.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有些兄弟已是杀人成性  动不动就挑衅\N{\fs16\fsp0}Hits became a habit. Guys would get into arguments over nothing.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:39.03,1:00:41.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,时常  转眼就死了一个人\N{\fs16\fsp0}Before you knew it, one was dead.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:41.40,1:00:43.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,彼此常以枪相对\N{\fs16\fsp0}They were shooting each other all the time.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:43.77,1:00:47.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,早已习以为常  不值得大惊小怪\N{\fs16\fsp0}Shooting people was a normal thing. It was no big deal.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:48.90,1:00:51.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们跟比利·贝兹的事可不是件小事情\N{\fs16\fsp0}We had a serious problem with Billy Batts.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:51.94,1:00:56.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,汤米杀的是个大人物  地位很高的\N{\fs16\fsp0}This was really a touchy thing. Tommy killed a made guy.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:56.21,1:00:59.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,贝兹是坎必诺家族的一员  这种人是不能随便杀的\N{\fs16\fsp0}Batts was part of the Gambino crew and was considered untouchable.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:00.52,1:01:04.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你得有充分的理由\N{\fs16\fsp0}Before you touched a made guy, you had to have a good reason.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:04.19,1:01:06.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你得有上面正式的许可\N{\fs16\fsp0}You had to have a sit-down and you'd better get an okay...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:07.09,1:01:09.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,否则  被杀的人就是你\N{\fs16\fsp0}or you'd be the one who got whacked.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:21.64,1:01:23.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,星期六是太太之夜\N{\fs16\fsp0}Saturday night was for wives...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:23.64,1:01:26.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,礼拜五是女朋友之夜\N{\fs16\fsp0}but Friday night at the Copa was for the girlfriends.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:28.61,1:01:30.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,上星期我们看了山米·戴维斯的秀\N{\fs16\fsp0}Last week, we saw Sammy Davis, Jr.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:31.05,1:01:33.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,太值得看了  好会表演\N{\fs16\fsp0}You got to see this show. What a performer.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:34.12,1:01:37.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他会模仿别人  听起来就跟真人一样\N{\fs16\fsp0}He does these impersonations. You'd think it was the real people.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:37.79,1:01:41.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,真令人难以相信  难怪白人女孩为他倾心\N{\fs16\fsp0}It's unbelievable. You could see how a white girl could fall for him.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:42.22,1:01:43.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,什么\N{\fs16\fsp0}What?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:43.96,1:01:48.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不是说我  只是有的女孩  像那个瑞典女孩\N{\fs16\fsp0}Not me. But you could see how some girls could. Like that Swedish girl.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:48.86,1:01:50.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,换句话说  你赞同那种黑白关系\N{\fs16\fsp0}So you condone that stuff.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:50.93,1:01:52.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,别那么认真\N{\fs16\fsp0}Take it easy.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:53.94,1:01:56.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不要间接跟黑人接吻\N{\fs16\fsp0}I don't want to be kissing Nat King Cole over here.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:57.01,1:01:58.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我又不是在说我自己\N{\fs16\fsp0}No, I'm not talking about me.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:00.34,1:02:02.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他很有个性\N{\fs16\fsp0}But, you know, he's got personality.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:02.41,1:02:04.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,个性\N{\fs16\fsp0}Personality?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:05.31,1:02:08.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他非常有才气  我完全明白\N{\fs16\fsp0}He's talented. I understand what you're saying.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:08.48,1:02:11.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不过你要注意你所说的话  别人很容易误会\N{\fs16\fsp0}But watch what you say. People get the wrong impression.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:12.02,1:02:14.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我只是说他很有才气  令人难以相信\N{\fs16\fsp0}I just said he was talented, you're unbelievable.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:14.59,1:02:17.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你说够了吧  你说的我都懂\N{\fs16\fsp0}Just leave it alone now, I understand what you said.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:17.26,1:02:19.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他很有才气  就这样子\N{\fs16\fsp0}He's talented. Leave it at that.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:57.93,1:04:00.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,连给保利叔叔亲一下都不行\N{\fs16\fsp0}No? Not even Uncle Paulie?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:16.78,1:04:19.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你有没有听到什么消息\N{\fs16\fsp0}What did you hear about that thing?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:19.75,1:04:22.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 布鲁克林的事吗  - 不是  城中那家伙的事\N{\fs16\fsp0}- The Brooklyn thing? - No, the guy from downtown.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:23.45,1:04:26.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 克莉丝家附近那家伙吗  - 不是\N{\fs16\fsp0}- The guy from where Christie lived? - No.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:27.76,1:04:30.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,失踪的那个家伙  也就是曾经被警察逮捕定罪的那个家伙\N{\fs16\fsp0}The guy who disappeared, the one they made the beef on.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:31.73,1:04:33.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 你认得那个人吗  - 是呀\N{\fs16\fsp0}- Know the guy I mean? - Yeah.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:33.83,1:04:37.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他叫贝兹  他手下的人像疯了一样到处找他\N{\fs16\fsp0}His name was Batts. His people are driving everyone crazy looking for him.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:38.07,1:04:39.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没人知道他去哪里了\N{\fs16\fsp0}Nobody knows what happened to him.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:39.93,1:04:44.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有天晚上他到我店来过  他走之后就失踪了\N{\fs16\fsp0}He came into the joint that night and then just disappeared. That was it.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:45.84,1:04:49.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好  眼睛放亮一点  他们一直来跟我啰嗦\N{\fs16\fsp0}All right. Keep your eyes open. They're busting my balls over it.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:50.48,1:04:52.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 好吗  - 我会的\N{\fs16\fsp0}- All right? - Yeah.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:54.98,1:04:57.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好吧  大家来吃吧\N{\fs16\fsp0}Okay, everybody, let's eat.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:03.32,1:05:04.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我要我的钱\N{\fs16\fsp0}I want my money.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:06.03,1:05:07.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他欠我\N{\fs16\fsp0}He owes it.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:16.27,1:05:19.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还记得郊外那件事吗\N{\fs16\fsp0}You know that thing we took care of upstate?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:19.24,1:05:22.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 保利刚才还提到呢  - 我们得把他挖出来\N{\fs16\fsp0}- Paulie was talking about that. - Got to get it out of there.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:23.24,1:05:25.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那块地就要开始建大厦了\N{\fs16\fsp0}They just sold the property to make condominiums.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:26.01,1:05:29.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 已经六个月了呀  - 我们要马上把他移走\N{\fs16\fsp0}- It's been six months. - We got to get it out of there right away.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:42.13,1:05:46.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,亨利  快点好不好  我妈要给我们炸香肠吃\N{\fs16\fsp0}Henry, hurry up. My mother's making fried peppers and sausage for us.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:50.10,1:05:52.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 这有只手臂  - 很好笑呀\N{\fs16\fsp0}- Here's an arm. - Very funny, guys.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:52.51,1:05:53.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这儿有条腿\N{\fs16\fsp0}Here's a leg.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:54.08,1:05:55.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这儿有只翅膀\N{\fs16\fsp0}Here's a wing.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:56.28,1:06:00.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你喜欢什么  大腿还是翅膀  心还是肺\N{\fs16\fsp0}What do you like, the leg or the wing? Or you still go for the hearts and lungs?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:01.98,1:06:03.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,真臭死了\N{\fs16\fsp0}Oh, that's so bad.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:10.53,1:06:12.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,车子怎么了\N{\fs16\fsp0}What happened to the car?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:12.86,1:06:14.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我撞死了一只臭鼬\N{\fs16\fsp0}I hit a skunk, all right?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:14.70,1:06:16.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,跟妈妈走吧\N{\fs16\fsp0}Go with your mother.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:17.47,1:06:19.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,真是恶心死了  亨利\N{\fs16\fsp0}It's disgusting, Henry.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:23.20,1:06:26.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我把珍丽丝安顿在离家不远的公寓里\N{\fs16\fsp0}I set up Janice in an apartment around the corner from The Suite.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:26.51,1:06:29.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那样我每星期可以在她那儿过夜一两次\N{\fs16\fsp0}That way I was able to stay over a couple of nights a week.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:29.31,1:06:30.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是新买的古董台灯\N{\fs16\fsp0}This is my new antique lamp.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:30.71,1:06:33.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,凯伦从来不过问我的事  她只在家里带孩子\N{\fs16\fsp0}Karen was home with the kids. She never asked questions.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:33.95,1:06:35.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,家具都是设计家摩瑞斯的作品\N{\fs16\fsp0}The furniture's all Maurice Valencia.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:35.95,1:06:37.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好像是罗马的作品\N{\fs16\fsp0}Looks like Roma.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:37.72,1:06:39.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这些都是真丝的  从暹罗进口的\N{\fs16\fsp0}This is all silk. This is from Siam.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:41.99,1:06:43.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,来看我的卧房\N{\fs16\fsp0}Come see my bedroom.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:44.49,1:06:48.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 汤米  你抱他一下好吗  - 我今晚就把他吃掉\N{\fs16\fsp0}- Tommy, will you take him? - I'll eat this fucking dog tonight.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:52.30,1:06:54.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,喜欢那个水晶球吗\N{\fs16\fsp0}Love that crystal ball or what?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:55.97,1:06:58.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们多数时间都是在这里消磨的\N{\fs16\fsp0}This is where we spend most of our time.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:00.71,1:07:03.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那盆花插得真美\N{\fs16\fsp0}I love the floral arrangements.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:05.01,1:07:06.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,法国货呀\N{\fs16\fsp0}French.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:06.21,1:07:10.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,珍丽丝只顾和我一起玩乐  工作上出轨了\N{\fs16\fsp0}Janice and I were having so much fun, she started screwing up at work.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:10.28,1:07:12.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我只好去给她老板一点教训\N{\fs16\fsp0}I had to straighten out her boss a little bit.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:12.92,1:07:16.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,珍丽丝喜欢怎么做  她就可以怎么做  你懂吗\N{\fs16\fsp0}Janice can do what she wants to do. Got it?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:16.66,1:07:21.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,随便你往哪里跑  如果你再挂我的电话  你试试看\N{\fs16\fsp0}Just try to run. Hang up once more, and you'll deal with me.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:26.60,1:07:28.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好了啦  放开她\N{\fs16\fsp0}Come on, get off of her.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:29.17,1:07:30.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你真是个野兽\N{\fs16\fsp0}You're an animal.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:43.82,1:07:47.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,小蜘蛛  过来带杯酒给我\N{\fs16\fsp0}Spider, on your way over here, bring me a Cutty and water.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:50.02,1:07:52.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 你们吃饭了没有  - 我饿死了\N{\fs16\fsp0}- Did you guys eat? - I'm starving.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:53.83,1:07:56.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 打就打啦  - 那些你也能打\N{\fs16\fsp0}- I'll play these. - You'll play those?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:56.26,1:07:58.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我有口吃吗  那些我都打\N{\fs16\fsp0}Do I stutter? I play those.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:02.14,1:08:04.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我是什么  我不存在呀\N{\fs16\fsp0}What am I? A mirage?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:04.37,1:08:07.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,什么  我的酒呢\N{\fs16\fsp0}Where's my fucking drink? I asked you for a drink.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:07.18,1:08:09.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 你有说要酒吗  - 我刚才跟你说要酒呀\N{\fs16\fsp0}- You wanted a drink? - I asked you for one.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:10.01,1:08:12.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我以为你是说  我不用了  小蜘蛛\N{\fs16\fsp0}I thought you said, "I'm all right, Spider."{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:13.71,1:08:15.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你把我例入不用理会的名单吗\N{\fs16\fsp0}Am I on a pay-no-mind list?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:15.82,1:08:20.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不是的  我听到有人叫  小蜘蛛  小蜘蛛\N{\fs16\fsp0}No, I heard someone say "Spider, Spider."{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:20.19,1:08:23.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 我以为是亨利在叫吧  - 你简直是又笨又口吃的蠢货\N{\fs16\fsp0}- I thought it was Henry. - You're a mumbling, stuttering little fuck.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:23.66,1:08:25.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我以为你说  我不用了  小蜘蛛\N{\fs16\fsp0}I thought you said, "I'm all right, Spider."{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:25.89,1:08:27.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你麻烦大了\N{\fs16\fsp0}You ain't all right.{\r}
