Dialogue: 0,1:15:20.37,1:15:22.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是什么滋味  凯伦\N{\fs16\fsp0}How does it feel, Karen?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:38.96,1:15:40.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我很抱歉\N{\fs16\fsp0}I'm sorry!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:47.94,1:15:49.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,吉米  你好吗\N{\fs16\fsp0}Hi, Jimmy! How are you?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:50.74,1:15:53.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 看来挺好嘛  - 谢谢  很高兴见到你\N{\fs16\fsp0}- Looking good. - Thank you. Good to see you.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:53.91,1:15:56.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 保利  - 甜心  你好吧\N{\fs16\fsp0}- Hi, Paulie! - Hi, honey. How are you?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:56.54,1:15:57.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,很好呀\N{\fs16\fsp0}Good.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:15:57.71,1:16:00.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 你去帮我买包香烟好吗  - 好\N{\fs16\fsp0}- Why don't you go get cigarettes, okay? - Sure.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:01.25,1:16:03.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 你们需要什么吗  - 不用\N{\fs16\fsp0}- Any of you need anything? - I'm all right.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:04.08,1:16:06.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 你们要喝什么吗  啤酒  - 不用\N{\fs16\fsp0}- Want anything to drink? A beer? - No.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:07.12,1:16:09.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 来点中国菜  - 不用  过来坐下\N{\fs16\fsp0}- Chinese food? - No, come on, sit down.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:16.46,1:16:18.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,凯伦来看我了\N{\fs16\fsp0}Karen came to the house.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:19.13,1:16:19.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她很气愤\N{\fs16\fsp0}She's very upset.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:20.33,1:16:22.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这样很不好  你要把你们的问题解决一下\N{\fs16\fsp0}This is no good. You gotta straighten this thing out.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:22.77,1:16:26.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们一定要冷静  她什么事都做得出来\N{\fs16\fsp0}We got to have calm now. We don't know what the hell she's gonna do.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:26.21,1:16:28.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她已经歇斯底里了  很容易兴奋\N{\fs16\fsp0}She's getting all hysterical. She gets very excited.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:28.61,1:16:32.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她很激动  你就得慢慢来  别忘了还有孩子\N{\fs16\fsp0}She's wild. And you got to take it easy. You got children.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:33.45,1:16:36.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不是说要你马上回去  不过你还是非回去不可\N{\fs16\fsp0}I'm not saying you gotta back to her this minute, but you gotta go back.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:37.02,1:16:39.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你别无选择  你得注意自己的形象\N{\fs16\fsp0}It's the only way. You gotta keep up appearances.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:39.62,1:16:42.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,凯伦跟美琪每天到我家来诉苦\N{\fs16\fsp0}The two of them come over every day, commiserating.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:42.26,1:16:44.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我受不了了\N{\fs16\fsp0}I can't have it.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:45.39,1:16:47.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,亨利  我不能那样\N{\fs16\fsp0}I can't do it, Henry.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:47.90,1:16:50.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没人说你不能做你喜欢的\N{\fs16\fsp0}Nobody says that you can't do what you wanna do.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:51.13,1:16:53.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们知道是怎么回事\N{\fs16\fsp0}We all know that. I mean, this is what it is.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:53.93,1:16:56.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可是你要面面俱到\N{\fs16\fsp0}We know what it is. You have to do the right thing.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:56.87,1:16:59.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你不能不顾到你的家庭  懂吗\N{\fs16\fsp0}You have to go home to the family, you understand?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:16:59.37,1:17:01.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你就是得回家  知道吗\N{\fs16\fsp0}You got to go home, okay? Look at me.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:02.28,1:17:04.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你就是得回家  放聪明一点\N{\fs16\fsp0}You gotta go home. Smarten up.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:05.21,1:17:06.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 好吗  - 好吧\N{\fs16\fsp0}- All right? - All right.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:06.91,1:17:08.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我会跟凯伦讲讲\N{\fs16\fsp0}I'm gonna talk to Karen.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:08.62,1:17:12.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我会把事摆平  我知道该对她说些什么\N{\fs16\fsp0}I'll straighten this out. I know just what to say to her.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:12.65,1:17:14.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我会说你愿意回去\N{\fs16\fsp0}I'm gonna tell her you'll go back to her...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:14.82,1:17:17.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一切跟以前一样\N{\fs16\fsp0}and it'll be just the way it was when you were first married...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:17.89,1:17:19.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我会说得很动人  会很圆满的\N{\fs16\fsp0}your romance, it's gonna be beautiful.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:19.89,1:17:21.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,跟她谈  我很有把握\N{\fs16\fsp0}I know how to talk to her, especially to her.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:22.10,1:17:24.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,吉米跟汤米要到天波城\N{\fs16\fsp0}Jimmy and Tommy are going down to Tampa this weekend...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:24.73,1:17:25.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,去帮我拿东西\N{\fs16\fsp0}to pick up something for me.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:26.03,1:17:27.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你代替汤米和吉米去好了\N{\fs16\fsp0}Instead, you go with Jimmy.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:27.90,1:17:29.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你来和我一起去吧\N{\fs16\fsp0}You come with me, we'll go down.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:29.30,1:17:31.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好好玩玩  让自己轻松一下\N{\fs16\fsp0}Have a good time. Take some time for yourself. Relax.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:32.04,1:17:33.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在太阳底下好好休息\N{\fs16\fsp0}Sit in the sun. Take a couple days off.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:34.01,1:17:35.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 我们会玩得很愉快的  - 好好玩\N{\fs16\fsp0}- We'll have a good time. - Enjoy yourselves.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:36.04,1:17:38.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但当你回来时  你就要回到凯伦身边\N{\fs16\fsp0}And when you come back, you go back to Karen.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:39.31,1:17:41.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,拜托你了  别无他法\N{\fs16\fsp0}Please, there's no other way.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:41.18,1:17:43.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你不能离婚  我们不是禽兽\N{\fs16\fsp0}You're not gonna get a divorce. We're not animali.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:43.95,1:17:46.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们不会离婚  她永远不会同意离婚\N{\fs16\fsp0}No divorce. She'll never divorce him.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:48.32,1:17:51.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她会杀了他  但不会跟他离婚\N{\fs16\fsp0}She'll kill him, but she won't divorce him.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:55.53,1:17:57.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你到底付不付\N{\fs16\fsp0}You gonna pay us?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:17:57.30,1:18:00.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,佛罗里达州天波市  两天后
Dialogue: 0,1:18:03.57,1:18:06.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 你付钱呀  - 快把钱给我们\N{\fs16\fsp0}- You gonna pay? - Give us the fucking money!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:07.14,1:18:09.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我没有  我真的没有\N{\fs16\fsp0}I can't, I swear.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:10.74,1:18:12.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们走\N{\fs16\fsp0}Let's go.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:13.61,1:18:15.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,天波市立动物园
Dialogue: 0,1:18:20.59,1:18:23.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 我们把这个杂种丢给狮子  - 不要呀\N{\fs16\fsp0}- We'll throw the bastard to the lions. - No!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:23.42,1:18:26.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,什么狮子  我可不要进去  吉米\N{\fs16\fsp0}What fucking lions? I ain't going near any lions, Jimmy!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:26.29,1:18:28.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 把他丢过分界沟就行了  - 那好\N{\fs16\fsp0}- Let's throw him over the moat. - All right.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:28.80,1:18:30.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我一定把钱给你们\N{\fs16\fsp0}I'll get the money!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:30.33,1:18:32.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一定要有人被喂狮子\N{\fs16\fsp0}They must really feed each other to the lions down there...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:33.13,1:18:34.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那家伙马上就付钱了\N{\fs16\fsp0}because the guy gave the money right up.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:35.04,1:18:36.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我对上帝发誓我会付钱\N{\fs16\fsp0}I swear to Christ, I'll get the money.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:36.84,1:18:38.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们在赛马场度周末\N{\fs16\fsp0}We got to spend the rest of the weekend at the track.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:39.37,1:18:40.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们不是开玩笑的\N{\fs16\fsp0}Yeah. They mean business.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:40.87,1:18:43.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,接着发生的真的难以相信\N{\fs16\fsp0}Then, I couldn't believe what happened.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:43.91,1:18:46.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当我们回到家的时候  我们已经是新闻人物了\N{\fs16\fsp0}When we got home, we were all over the newspaper.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:46.61,1:18:49.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,最初  我根本不知道那边会跟媒体有牵连\N{\fs16\fsp0}At first, I didn't even know why we got picked up.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:49.98,1:18:52.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,后来才知道被我们揍的人的姐姐\N{\fs16\fsp0}Then I found out that the guy we roughed up...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:52.29,1:18:55.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,是FBI打字员\N{\fs16\fsp0}turned out to have a sister working as a typist for the FBI.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:55.82,1:18:58.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,谁会想到天下有那么巧的事\N{\fs16\fsp0}Who could believe it? Of all the fucking people.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:18:58.76,1:19:02.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她把吉米  我  甚至她弟弟全都抖出来了\N{\fs16\fsp0}She gave up everybody: Jimmy, me, even her brother.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:03.46,1:19:06.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,陪审团花了六小时  裁决我们有罪\N{\fs16\fsp0}It took the jury six hours to bring us in guilty.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:06.47,1:19:09.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,法官判我和吉米每人十年  好像在发糖果一样\N{\fs16\fsp0}The judge gave Jimmy and me 10 years like he was giving away candy.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:09.90,1:19:12.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,判处你们在国立监狱服刑十年\N{\fs16\fsp0}...ten years in a federal penitentiary.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:12.77,1:19:16.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在交给检察官\N{\fs16\fsp0}You will now be turned over to the U.S. Attorney General's office.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:20.28,1:19:22.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,来敬你一杯\N{\fs16\fsp0}Toast, guys.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:22.92,1:19:25.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一路平安  祝福你们早日出来\N{\fs16\fsp0}Good trip, good life, get out soon.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:25.42,1:19:27.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一切顺利\N{\fs16\fsp0}Good trip, sweetheart.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:30.22,1:19:32.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们会替你照顾家的\N{\fs16\fsp0}We'll watch the home front.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:33.79,1:19:36.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,替我问候那些口交的警卫\N{\fs16\fsp0}Say hello to those blow-job hacks.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:37.30,1:19:40.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,别忘了一有机会就占他们的便宜\N{\fs16\fsp0}Yeah, motherfuck them every chance you get.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:19:46.34,1:19:48.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有机会我会打电话给你\N{\fs16\fsp0}I'll call you when I get a chance.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:01.26,1:20:02.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,送我去监狱吧\N{\fs16\fsp0}Now take me to jail.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:07.23,1:20:10.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在监狱里  晚餐很重要\N{\fs16\fsp0}In prison, dinner was always a big thing.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:10.36,1:20:13.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,先来一道意大利面  接着或鱼或肉\N{\fs16\fsp0}We had a pasta course, and then we had a meat or a fish.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:14.50,1:20:17.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,保利因藐视法庭被判了一年  他负责准备工作\N{\fs16\fsp0}Paulie did the prep work. He was doing a year for contempt...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:17.57,1:20:19.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他有一套切大蒜的诀窍\N{\fs16\fsp0}and had this wonderful system for doing the garlic.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:20.07,1:20:23.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,用刀片切得很薄\N{\fs16\fsp0}He used a razor, and he used to slice it so thin...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:23.28,1:20:26.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,放在锅里  加上一点油就化了\N{\fs16\fsp0}that it used to liquefy in the pan with just a little oil.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:26.21,1:20:28.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那方法很好\N{\fs16\fsp0}It was a very good system.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:28.45,1:20:30.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,韦力掌管蕃茄汁\N{\fs16\fsp0}Vinnie was in charge of the tomato sauce.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:31.12,1:20:32.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,闻到了没有\N{\fs16\fsp0}Get the smell?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:32.69,1:20:35.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这肉丸里有三种肉\N{\fs16\fsp0}Three kinds of meat in the meatballs:{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:35.59,1:20:37.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有小牛肉  牛肉和猪肉\N{\fs16\fsp0}Veal, beef, and pork.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:37.99,1:20:40.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那好  反正猪肉是一定要的\N{\fs16\fsp0}Good, but you gotta have the pork.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:40.26,1:20:41.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那是主要的味道来源\N{\fs16\fsp0}That's the flavor.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:41.96,1:20:45.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我觉得他洋葱放多了  但味道还是很好\N{\fs16\fsp0}I felt he used too many onions, but it was still a very good sauce.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:45.60,1:20:48.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,韦力  不要放太多洋葱\N{\fs16\fsp0}Vinnie, don't put too many onions in the sauce.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:48.54,1:20:51.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我没放太多\N{\fs16\fsp0}I didn't put too much onions in, Paul.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:51.44,1:20:53.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只放了三个小的而已\N{\fs16\fsp0}Put three small onions, that's all I did.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:53.37,1:20:55.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,三个洋葱  那你放了几罐蕃茄酱\N{\fs16\fsp0}Three onions? How many cans of tomatoes you put in there?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:56.11,1:20:58.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 两大罐  - 你不需要放三个洋葱\N{\fs16\fsp0}- I put two big cans. - You don't need three onions.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:20:59.01,1:21:01.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,强尼煎牛排\N{\fs16\fsp0}Johnny Dio did the meat.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:01.18,1:21:03.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为没有烤箱  强尼用平底锅做菜\N{\fs16\fsp0}We had no broiler, so Johnny did everything in pans.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:03.95,1:21:06.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他每次都把屋子里弄得乌烟瘴气\N{\fs16\fsp0}It used to smell up the joint something awful...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:06.22,1:21:09.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,警卫都被熏死了  但他的牛排还真是不错\N{\fs16\fsp0}and the hacks used to die, but he still cooked a great steak.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:09.36,1:21:11.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 你的牛排要怎么样  - 半生的\N{\fs16\fsp0}- How do you like yours? - Medium rare.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:12.49,1:21:14.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,半生  贵族一个\N{\fs16\fsp0}Medium rare. An aristocrat.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:15.03,1:21:18.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,当你想到监狱  脑中就会出现像电影中那样\N{\fs16\fsp0}You know, when you think of prison you get pictures in your mind...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:18.97,1:21:22.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一排排的人被关在铁栏杆后面\N{\fs16\fsp0}of all those old movies with rows of guys behind bars.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:22.77,1:21:24.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对兄弟来说不是那样的\N{\fs16\fsp0}It wasn't like that for wiseguys.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:24.84,1:21:27.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,并不是那么槽  除了我很想念吉米\N{\fs16\fsp0}It really wasn't that bad, excepting that I missed Jimmy...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:27.67,1:21:29.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他在亚特兰大受刑\N{\fs16\fsp0}who was doing his time in Atlanta.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:29.24,1:21:31.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,顺便给我两块牛排  好不好\N{\fs16\fsp0}Give me two steaks while you're in there, all right?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:33.15,1:21:37.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在里面的人都是严格地在受刑  混在一起像猪一样\N{\fs16\fsp0}Everyone else in the joint was doing real time, mixed together, living like pigs.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:37.72,1:21:40.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,可是我们单独生活  一切都由我们控制\N{\fs16\fsp0}But we lived alone. We owned the joint.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:40.89,1:21:44.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,用球棒把那两个狗娘养的脸打烂了  认都认不出来\N{\fs16\fsp0}We batted them sons of bitches. You couldn't recognize them.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:44.46,1:21:45.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,太好了  活该\N{\fs16\fsp0}Good, they deserved it.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:45.96,1:21:49.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,虽然有些警卫不受贿  但他们也不会告发我们\N{\fs16\fsp0}Even the hacks we couldn't bribe would never rat on the guys we did.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:49.63,1:21:51.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这样才对  朋友邻居间应该互相尊重\N{\fs16\fsp0}...had respect. People loved one another.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:51.57,1:21:52.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,夜不闭户\N{\fs16\fsp0}They left their doors open.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:52.77,1:21:53.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,抱歉  久等了\N{\fs16\fsp0}Sorry it took so long.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:53.93,1:21:56.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那个瘦子警卫越来越令人讨厌了\N{\fs16\fsp0}The skinny guard's getting to be a real pain in the ass.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:56.57,1:21:59.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 是该给那个杂种一点教训了  - 我已经摆平了\N{\fs16\fsp0}- We're gonna have to do something. - I took care of him.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:21:59.97,1:22:01.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你带了些什么来\N{\fs16\fsp0}What'd you bring?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:01.84,1:22:03.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 面包  - 好\N{\fs16\fsp0}- Bread. - Good.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:03.64,1:22:05.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 才烤出来的  - 韦力  你的辣椒和洋葱有了\N{\fs16\fsp0}- Fresh. - Vinnie, I got your peppers and onions.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:06.08,1:22:08.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,香肠  火腿  还有很多奶酪\N{\fs16\fsp0}Salami, prosciutto, a lot of cheese.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:08.55,1:22:10.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还有呢  还有什么别的\N{\fs16\fsp0}Come on, what else?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:10.22,1:22:11.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 威士忌  - 好\N{\fs16\fsp0}- Scotch. - Nice.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:12.72,1:22:14.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 红酒  - 好了\N{\fs16\fsp0}- Some red wine. - Okay.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:14.89,1:22:16.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 我们可以吃了  - 我也拿了白葡萄酒\N{\fs16\fsp0}- Now we can eat. - I got some white, too.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:16.92,1:22:18.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,白葡萄酒也给我  太美了\N{\fs16\fsp0}Give me the white, too. Beautiful.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:18.86,1:22:21.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,来吧  伙计们  我们可以吃了  已经好了  韦力\N{\fs16\fsp0}Okay, boys, let's eat. Come on, it's ready, Vinnie.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:22.43,1:22:23.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这里还有些面包\N{\fs16\fsp0}Some more bread.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:23.70,1:22:26.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,明天我们吃三明治  你该节食了  韦力\N{\fs16\fsp0}Tomorrow we eat sandwiches. You got to go on a diet, Vinnie.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:26.53,1:22:28.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 你别开玩笑了  - 你最好听我的\N{\fs16\fsp0}- You must be kidding. - Believe me.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:37.88,1:22:39.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你在忙什么\N{\fs16\fsp0}What are you doing?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:44.62,1:22:46.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我也来一点\N{\fs16\fsp0}I'll take that.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:48.89,1:22:51.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 好  晚一点见  - 对\N{\fs16\fsp0}- All right, I'll catch you guys later. - Yeah.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:51.53,1:22:53.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,去公园散散步  是不是\N{\fs16\fsp0}You going for a walk in the park?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:22:55.36,1:22:58.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 好  下礼拜见  谢谢  - 好\N{\fs16\fsp0}- Okay, I'll catch you next week. Thanks. - Okay.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:01.30,1:23:03.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 还有没有  - 没了  全光了  周末愉快\N{\fs16\fsp0}- Is there any more? - No, that's it. Have a good weekend.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:04.07,1:23:05.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 谢啦  - 亨利  再见了\N{\fs16\fsp0}- Thanks. - You too, Henry.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:17.88,1:23:19.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,来\N{\fs16\fsp0}Come on.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:19.62,1:23:21.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好好站在这儿\N{\fs16\fsp0}You girls stay right here.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:22.09,1:23:25.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 你们两个牵着手  - 好了  一直走到前面去\N{\fs16\fsp0}- I want you to hold hands. - Okay, go right up to the front.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:25.66,1:23:27.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 走吧  - 你好吗\N{\fs16\fsp0}- Let's go. - How you doing?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:27.76,1:23:30.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 还行  你呢  - 很好  谢谢你\N{\fs16\fsp0}- Good, how are you? - Very well, thank you.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:42.24,1:23:44.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 你讲什么呀  - 我在登记簿上看到她的名字了\N{\fs16\fsp0}- What you talking about? - I saw her name in the register.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:44.98,1:23:47.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 老天呀  - 你要她来看你吗\N{\fs16\fsp0}- Jesus Christ. - You want her to visit you?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:47.21,1:23:51.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,让她为你哭整晚不睡  还写信给假释管理局\N{\fs16\fsp0}Let her stay up all night crying and writing letters to the parole board.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:51.18,1:23:54.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你以为我在这儿做什么  我在坐牢呀\N{\fs16\fsp0}What am I doing here? Where am I? I'm in jail.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:54.39,1:23:56.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不能阻止别人来看我呀\N{\fs16\fsp0}I can't stop people from coming to see me.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:23:56.76,1:24:00.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好呀  让她每星期替你偷运这些东西进来\N{\fs16\fsp0}Good, let her sneak this stuff in for you every week.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:00.19,1:24:04.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 让她每星期来和那些杂种警卫打交道  - 你这是干什么\N{\fs16\fsp0}- Let her fight these bastards every week! - Look what you're doing! Stop it!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:06.30,1:24:07.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,很抱歉\N{\fs16\fsp0}I'm sorry.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:08.03,1:24:10.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,让她来替你把这些狗屎运进来\N{\fs16\fsp0}Let her sneak this shit in for you.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:11.54,1:24:13.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你够了没有  凯伦\N{\fs16\fsp0}Will you stop it, Karen?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:13.84,1:24:16.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 让她去做所有的事嘛  - 够了\N{\fs16\fsp0}- Let her do it! - Stop it!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:24.58,1:24:27.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我好孤独  没有人要帮我\N{\fs16\fsp0}Nobody's helping me. I'm all alone.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:28.89,1:24:30.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,贝儿和摩里都破产了\N{\fs16\fsp0}Belle and Morrie are broke.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:31.32,1:24:34.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我向你的朋友利摩讨他欠你的钱\N{\fs16\fsp0}I asked your friend Remo for the money that he owes you.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:34.69,1:24:36.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你知道他说什么吗\N{\fs16\fsp0}You know what he told me?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:36.23,1:24:39.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他叫我把孩子们带到警察局去领救济金\N{\fs16\fsp0}He told me to take my kids down to the police station and get on welfare.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:40.00,1:24:41.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一切会过去的\N{\fs16\fsp0}It's gonna be okay.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:42.17,1:24:46.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就连保利  他出去后我也没见到他  我都没见到他们了\N{\fs16\fsp0}Even Paulie, since he got out, I've never seen him. I never see anybody anymore.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:46.44,1:24:49.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只有我们两个了\N{\fs16\fsp0}It's only you and me. That's what happens when you go away.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:49.38,1:24:53.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我告诉过你  一旦进了牢就孤立了  忘掉所有的人  忘掉保利\N{\fs16\fsp0}I told you that we're on our own. Forget everybody else. Forget Paulie.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:24:54.38,1:24:58.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他在保释期间是不会帮任何人做任何事的\N{\fs16\fsp0}As long as he's on parole, he doesn't want anybody doing anything.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:00.85,1:25:03.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 我受不了了  - 你能够忍受  听我说\N{\fs16\fsp0}- I can't do it. - Yes, you can. Listen to me.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:03.36,1:25:05.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你只要不断把东西带来\N{\fs16\fsp0}All I need is for you is to keep bringing me the stuff.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:06.03,1:25:08.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这里有个从匹兹堡来的  他会帮我销货\N{\fs16\fsp0}I got a guy in here from Pittsburgh who'll help me move it.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:08.80,1:25:10.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一个月后我们就安定了\N{\fs16\fsp0}In a month we're gonna be fine.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:10.52,1:25:13.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 我们不需要别人  - 我害怕\N{\fs16\fsp0}- We won't need anybody. - I'm afraid.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:13.17,1:25:15.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我怕万一保利知道你私下在贩毒\N{\fs16\fsp0}I'm afraid if Paulie finds out...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:15.27,1:25:16.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不是说了吗  不要担心保利\N{\fs16\fsp0}Don't worry about him.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:16.72,1:25:20.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他并没有帮我们呀  他有没有供应食物给我们\N{\fs16\fsp0}He is not helping us out. Is he putting any food on the table?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:21.44,1:25:22.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们只有彼此帮助\N{\fs16\fsp0}We've gotta help each other.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:23.08,1:25:26.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们的行动一定要特别特别小心\N{\fs16\fsp0}We've just gotta be really careful while we do it.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:31.42,1:25:33.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,别让我再听到她的名字\N{\fs16\fsp0}I don't want to hear a word about her anymore.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:34.09,1:25:35.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,永远不会了\N{\fs16\fsp0}Never.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:25:37.89,1:25:40.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,四年后
Dialogue: 0,1:26:00.21,1:26:01.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,爸爸\N{\fs16\fsp0}Daddy!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:03.48,1:26:05.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 我们好想念你  - 你会待下来吗\N{\fs16\fsp0}- We missed you. - Are you here to stay?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:05.92,1:26:09.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你看到我们的画没有  那张房子和彩虹是我画的\N{\fs16\fsp0}Did you see our pictures? I did the one with the house and rainbow.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:09.62,1:26:11.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,太阳是我画的\N{\fs16\fsp0}I did the sun.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:11.26,1:26:15.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我的合唱团两星期后有音乐会  你能来吗\N{\fs16\fsp0}My chorus concert is in two weeks. Are you coming?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:16.00,1:26:17.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,喜欢我们的房子吗\N{\fs16\fsp0}Do you like the house?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:19.13,1:26:21.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,凯伦  收拾行李  我们要搬家了\N{\fs16\fsp0}Karen, get packed. We're moving out of here.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:21.33,1:26:22.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,怎么搬\N{\fs16\fsp0}With what?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:22.60,1:26:25.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不用担心  去找新房子就好了\N{\fs16\fsp0}Don't worry, with what. Just start looking for a new house.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:25.87,1:26:29.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,明早我要去匹兹堡  那边有几个人欠我一万五千元\N{\fs16\fsp0}I got to go to Pittsburgh in the morning. Those guys there owe me $15,000.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:29.44,1:26:31.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们没事了  我都安排好了\N{\fs16\fsp0}We'll be all right. I got things lined up.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:31.54,1:26:34.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,匹兹堡  你明天要去向你的假释官报到呀\N{\fs16\fsp0}Pittsburgh? You have to go see your parole officer tomorrow.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:34.38,1:26:37.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,凯伦  不要操心了  一切都会没问题的\N{\fs16\fsp0}Don't worry about it. Everything's gonna be fine.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:37.98,1:26:40.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 谁要去保利伯伯家  - 我\N{\fs16\fsp0}- Who wants to go to Uncle Paulie's? - Me!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:50.66,1:26:52.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你要什么\N{\fs16\fsp0}What do you want?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:52.50,1:26:54.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,甜心  让妈妈好好吃饭\N{\fs16\fsp0}Sweetheart, let Mommy eat.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:26:58.00,1:27:00.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,气色不错  牢里有吃得这么好吗\N{\fs16\fsp0}You look good. Did you eat this good in the joint?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:03.01,1:27:04.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不要再搞那些勾当了\N{\fs16\fsp0}I don't want any more of that shit.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:05.05,1:27:06.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,什么勾当\N{\fs16\fsp0}What shit?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:06.21,1:27:08.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 离那些垃圾远一点  - 保利\N{\fs16\fsp0}- Just stay away from the garbage. - Look, Paulie...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:08.98,1:27:12.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你在里面做了我不管  你是身不由己\N{\fs16\fsp0}I'm not talking about what you did inside. You did what you had to do.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:12.35,1:27:14.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我指现在  从现在  从这里开始\N{\fs16\fsp0}I'm talking about now. From now. Here and now.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:15.96,1:27:18.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 我怎么会搞那些  - 不要把我当傻瓜\N{\fs16\fsp0}- Why would I get into that? - Don't make a jerk out of me.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:18.86,1:27:20.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,千万不要\N{\fs16\fsp0}Just don't do it.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:24.16,1:27:27.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在  我要跟你谈吉米  你要注意他\N{\fs16\fsp0}I want to talk to you about Jimmy. You gotta watch out for him.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:27.30,1:27:30.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他很能赚钱  但他太狂了  太冒险了\N{\fs16\fsp0}He's a good earner, but he's wild, takes too many chances.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:30.20,1:27:32.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我了解吉米  你想我会像他那样冒险吗\N{\fs16\fsp0}I know Jimmy. You think I would take chances like him?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:32.84,1:27:34.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,汤米也是个好孩子  但他太疯了\N{\fs16\fsp0}Tommy's a good kid, but he's crazy.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:34.77,1:27:36.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他是个牛仔  他样样都想表现\N{\fs16\fsp0}He's a cowboy. He's got too much to prove.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:36.68,1:27:38.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你不能不自己小心\N{\fs16\fsp0}You gotta watch out for kids like this.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:38.48,1:27:41.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我太清楚他们的个性了  我只利用他们做些事\N{\fs16\fsp0}I know what they are. I only use them for certain things.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:41.25,1:27:43.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不要像盖比那样被人糟蹋  你明白吗\N{\fs16\fsp0}I ain't gonna get fucked like Gribbs, you understand?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:43.95,1:27:48.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,盖比已经70岁了  他将老死狱中  那不是我所要的\N{\fs16\fsp0}Gribbs is 70 years old. The fucking guy's gonna die in prison. I don't need that.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:48.62,1:27:52.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以我现在警告每一个人  连我儿子在内\N{\fs16\fsp0}So I'm warning everybody. Everybody. Could be my son, could be anybody.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:53.03,1:27:55.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就因为盖比手下的人\N{\fs16\fsp0}Gribbs got 20 years just for saying hello to some fuck...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:55.73,1:27:57.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在他背后贩毒  他被判20年\N{\fs16\fsp0}who was sneaking behind his back, selling junk.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:27:58.00,1:28:00.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我绝不容许这种事发生在我身上  你懂了吗\N{\fs16\fsp0}I don't need that. That won't happen to me, understand?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:00.60,1:28:02.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你能提早出来  是因为我给你找了份工作\N{\fs16\fsp0}You know you're out early because I got you a job.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:02.90,1:28:04.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不要整天被条子监视  明白吗\N{\fs16\fsp0}I don't need this heat, you understand that?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:05.07,1:28:08.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果你看到任何人在贩毒  你一定要来告诉我\N{\fs16\fsp0}You see anybody fucking around with this shit you're gonna tell me, right?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:09.14,1:28:10.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不管是谁\N{\fs16\fsp0}That means anybody.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:10.34,1:28:11.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对不对\N{\fs16\fsp0}All right.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:11.51,1:28:13.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对  当然\N{\fs16\fsp0}Yeah. Of course.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:20.69,1:28:24.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我花了一个星期明查暗访  才把那批匹兹堡货卖掉\N{\fs16\fsp0}Took me about a week of sneaking around before I could unload the Pittsburgh stuff.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:24.79,1:28:27.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不过我着实赚了一大笔\N{\fs16\fsp0}But when I did, it was a real score.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:27.43,1:28:29.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我开始利用珊蒂的家来混合毒品\N{\fs16\fsp0}I started using Sandy's place to mix the stuff.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:30.13,1:28:32.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,虽然她吸的比她配的还多\N{\fs16\fsp0}And even with Sandy snorting more than she mixed...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:32.73,1:28:35.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但还是利润极大的生意\N{\fs16\fsp0}I could see that this was a really good business.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:35.54,1:28:37.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,第二个礼拜我就赚了一万两千元\N{\fs16\fsp0}I made $12,000 in my second week.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:38.54,1:28:41.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,为我的房子付了头期款  事情越来越顺利了\N{\fs16\fsp0}I had a down payment on my house and things were really rolling.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:41.78,1:28:46.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我只要偶尔告诉珊蒂我爱她就好了\N{\fs16\fsp0}All I had to do was every once in a while tell Sandy that I loved her.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:49.62,1:28:51.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这种安排太完美了\N{\fs16\fsp0}But it was perfect, I'm telling you.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:51.85,1:28:54.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只要货是从匹兹堡来的\N{\fs16\fsp0}As long as I kept getting the stuff from Pittsburgh...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:54.39,1:28:56.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,保利绝不可能发觉\N{\fs16\fsp0}I knew Paulie would never find out.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:28:56.26,1:29:00.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,几个礼拜之后生意做大了  我一个人处理不了\N{\fs16\fsp0}Within a couple of weeks, it got so big I needed some help.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:00.49,1:29:03.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就把吉米和汤米拉了进来\N{\fs16\fsp0}So I got Jimmy and Tommy to come in with me.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:03.66,1:29:05.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,真够棒的\N{\fs16\fsp0}It's fucking great.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:05.40,1:29:06.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,康威先生\N{\fs16\fsp0}Mr. Conway.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:12.47,1:29:14.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 你薪水单带来没有  - 有\N{\fs16\fsp0}- Bring your pay slips? - Yeah.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:14.47,1:29:17.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,保释部
Dialogue: 0,1:29:17.40,1:29:19.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,兴建工程花了四个半月\N{\fs16\fsp0}Four and a half months of dirt.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:20.95,1:29:22.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 真好呀  - 撑过来了\N{\fs16\fsp0}- It's so good. - I did it.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:24.08,1:29:26.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 你喜欢吗  - 真是太棒了\N{\fs16\fsp0}- Do you love it? - It's wonderful.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:27.12,1:29:30.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这个订做的  你坐坐看  贝儿\N{\fs16\fsp0}And this we just had to have made special. Go ahead, sit in it, Belle.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:31.06,1:29:33.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,有的坐下去真不舒服\N{\fs16\fsp0}The others you couldn't even sit in.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:33.79,1:29:35.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好了  准备好\N{\fs16\fsp0}Okay, you ready?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:35.46,1:29:37.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,看着石壁\N{\fs16\fsp0}Watch the wall with the rock.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:45.27,1:29:48.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,电工特别设计的\N{\fs16\fsp0}The electricians did it special. Come on.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:49.24,1:29:51.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,来呀  来这边\N{\fs16\fsp0}Come on. All right.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:51.18,1:29:54.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这是进口货  两件组合起来的\N{\fs16\fsp0}This was imported. It came in two pieces. Do you believe what they can do?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:54.95,1:29:56.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不错\N{\fs16\fsp0}It's nice, huh?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:56.45,1:29:58.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,亨利  到这边来  你跟吉米商量过了没有\N{\fs16\fsp0}Henry, come over here. Did you and Jimmy talk?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:29:58.65,1:30:01.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我跟他说过了  他会仔细研究这件事的\N{\fs16\fsp0}I talked to him, and he's looking into everything.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:01.29,1:30:04.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这会让上次法国航空的劫案看起来像儿童故事\N{\fs16\fsp0}This'll make the Air France haul look like goddamn peanuts.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:04.66,1:30:06.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 小声点  - 你确定他会下手  对吗\N{\fs16\fsp0}- Come on. - He's gonna do it, right?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:07.09,1:30:09.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不是说了吗  他要好好研究一下\N{\fs16\fsp0}I told you. He'll check everything out.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:09.36,1:30:11.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,然后再做决定  没有任何承诺\N{\fs16\fsp0}He's looking into it. We'll see what happens. No promises.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:11.77,1:30:16.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我知道  你知道吗  那儿有好几百万\N{\fs16\fsp0}I know. Do you understand? There's millions in there. And I've been...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:16.30,1:30:19.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想对这批货下手想得都快吐血了  我栽培这个家伙两年了\N{\fs16\fsp0}bleeding for this caper, been cultivating this son of a bitch for two years.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:20.04,1:30:23.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这家伙欠我两万块  一辈子就一次  我可以退休了\N{\fs16\fsp0}He owes me $20,000. Once in a lifetime. I could retire.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:23.24,1:30:27.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不用再为钱操心  我的好梦就要成真了\N{\fs16\fsp0}No more nut every week. No more bullshit. My dream comes true.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:27.65,1:30:29.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,来吧  我们来喝一杯吧\N{\fs16\fsp0}Morrie, let's get a drink.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:29.72,1:30:32.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这就是吉米召集在一起\N{\fs16\fsp0}These are the guys that Jimmy put together for what turned out to be...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:32.95,1:30:36.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,犯下美国历史上最大劫案 德航劫案 的一批人\N{\fs16\fsp0}the biggest heist in American history: The Lufthansa heist.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:38.09,1:30:40.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,汤米跟卡本负责抓住门口警卫\N{\fs16\fsp0}Tommy and Carbone were gonna grab the outside guard...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:40.96,1:30:43.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,逼他开大门\N{\fs16\fsp0}and make him get us in the front door.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:44.73,1:30:48.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,法国仔和周佛负责把工作人员集中在一起\N{\fs16\fsp0}Frenchy and Joe Buddha had to round up the workers.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:48.57,1:30:52.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,强尼负责把货绑起来  以免触到警铃\N{\fs16\fsp0}Johnny Roastbeef had to keep them all tied up and away from the alarms.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:53.34,1:30:55.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就连史达克也被拉进来了\N{\fs16\fsp0}Even Stacks Edwards got in on it.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:55.71,1:30:59.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他常弹吉他  大家都喜欢他\N{\fs16\fsp0}He used to hang around the lounge and play guitar. Everybody loved Stacks.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:30:59.41,1:31:01.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他的任务是偷辆大卡车\N{\fs16\fsp0}What he was supposed to do was steal the panel truck...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:31:02.02,1:31:05.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,事后由纽泽西州朋友处理掉\N{\fs16\fsp0}and afterwards compact it by a friend of ours out in Jersey.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:31:05.32,1:31:07.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只有摩里真的烦死人了\N{\fs16\fsp0}Only Morrie was driving us nuts.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:31:07.85,1:31:09.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,摩里  喝一杯酒  然后闭嘴\N{\fs16\fsp0}Morrie, have a drink and shut up.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:31:10.02,1:31:13.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为这次的劫案是他从中拉线的\N{\fs16\fsp0}Just because he set this up, he felt he could bust Jimmy's balls...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:31:13.26,1:31:15.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,摩里就以为他可以向吉米预支是理所当然的事\N{\fs16\fsp0}for an advance on the money we were going to steal.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:31:15.96,1:31:19.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他并没有什么其他的意思  他就是这样的人\N{\fs16\fsp0}He didn't mean anything by it. That's just the way he was.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:31:26.41,1:31:30.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我让每个人都替我做事  就连以前的婴儿保姆也在内\N{\fs16\fsp0}I had everybody working for me. Even our old baby-sitter, Lois Byrd.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:31:33.55,1:31:35.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,飞机还稳吧\N{\fs16\fsp0}Did you have a good flight?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:31:35.22,1:31:37.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我恨匹兹堡  你在哪里找到那些烂人的\N{\fs16\fsp0}I hate Pittsburgh. Where did you find such creeps?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:31:37.85,1:31:39.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,好啦  没那么糟啦\N{\fs16\fsp0}Come on, they're not that bad.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:31:41.25,1:31:43.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,跑这一趟是值得的  对吗\N{\fs16\fsp0}And it's worth it, isn't it?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:31:43.22,1:31:45.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你上礼拜用的是不是这个婴儿\N{\fs16\fsp0}Is this the same baby you used last week?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:31:45.76,1:31:48.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不  上次是我姐姐的婴儿  这次是狄娜的\N{\fs16\fsp0}No, that one was my sister's. This is Deirdra's.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:31:49.80,1:31:50.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,打哈欠了\N{\fs16\fsp0}Big yawn.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:31:51.13,1:31:52.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,她长得好像你呀\N{\fs16\fsp0}She looks just like you.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:31:53.53,1:31:55.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,空中小姐也这么说\N{\fs16\fsp0}That's what the stewardess said.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:32:08.65,1:32:10.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,别那么狠好不好  珊蒂\N{\fs16\fsp0}Take it easy, Sandy.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:32:10.62,1:32:13.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,饶了我吧  我们这里有的是呀\N{\fs16\fsp0}Come on, give me a break. You got enough here to go around.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:32:13.52,1:32:16.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,少吸一点  你还有一整天  一次太多就不够用了\N{\fs16\fsp0}You got all day. Just make it last, all right? Take it easy.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:32:17.32,1:32:19.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 我得走了  - 你去哪里\N{\fs16\fsp0}- I got to go. - Where are you going?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:32:19.29,1:32:23.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不要跟我争  你知道我要去办事  操  我的车钥匙呢\N{\fs16\fsp0}Don't start. You know I gotta go do this thing. Fuck, where are my keys?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:32:24.70,1:32:26.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就在那里\N{\fs16\fsp0}Over there.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:32:26.23,1:32:27.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,真够乱的  像猪窝一样\N{\fs16\fsp0}It's a mess. It's like a pig pen.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:32:28.10,1:32:30.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,洗碗机买来是做什么的\N{\fs16\fsp0}What do you think I got you the dishwasher for?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:32:30.30,1:32:32.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我讨厌洗碗  弄坏我指甲\N{\fs16\fsp0}I hate doing the dishes. Fucks up my nails.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:32:32.27,1:32:34.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不管你讨不讨厌洗碗  你要放聪明点\N{\fs16\fsp0}How could you hate it? You got to be smart.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:32:34.17,1:32:37.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就凭这些白粉  被抓到了我们就别想出来了\N{\fs16\fsp0}Look at all this powder around here. That could put us away forever.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:32:37.48,1:32:39.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 别这么紧张嘛  - 你想干什么\N{\fs16\fsp0}- Loosen up. - What are you doing?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:32:40.98,1:32:44.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 我得走了  - 你哪儿也不用去\N{\fs16\fsp0}- You know, I gotta... - You don't have to go anywhere.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:32:45.45,1:32:46.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,让他们等\N{\fs16\fsp0}Make them wait.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:32:56.33,1:32:59.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,今晨黎明前  肯尼迪机场的德国航空货运站被劫\N{\fs16\fsp0}Nobody knows for sure just how much was taken in the daring pre-dawn raid...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:33:00.07,1:33:02.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没人能确定被劫的数目\N{\fs16\fsp0}at the Lufthansa cargo terminal at Kennedy Airport.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:33:02.84,1:33:06.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,FBI说是两百万  航空警察说四百万\N{\fs16\fsp0}The FBI says $2 million, Port Authority Police say $4 million...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:33:09.91,1:33:11.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,吉米\N{\fs16\fsp0}Jimmy!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:33:12.15,1:33:13.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们这些狗娘养的\N{\fs16\fsp0}Those sons of bitches!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:33:14.15,1:33:16.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在肯尼迪机场被劫的现场转播\N{\fs16\fsp0}...from the scene of the heist at JFK.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:33:16.65,1:33:20.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,看起来也许是本市历年来最大的一宗劫案\N{\fs16\fsp0}It looks like a big one. Maybe the biggest this town has ever seen.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:33:22.19,1:33:24.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,过来  过来\N{\fs16\fsp0}Come here, you! Come here!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:33:25.43,1:33:28.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,看看这个天才  这是个天才\N{\fs16\fsp0}Look at this genius. This genius!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:33:32.57,1:33:34.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,圣诞快乐\N{\fs16\fsp0}Merry Christmas.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:33:39.34,1:33:41.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 哈罗  这是谁呀  - 这是我太太\N{\fs16\fsp0}- Hello, who's this? - That's my wife.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:33:42.34,1:33:45.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你过来  给你看一样东西\N{\fs16\fsp0}Come here. I want to show you something, Jimmy.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:33:48.35,1:33:49.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,它美吧\N{\fs16\fsp0}Isn't she gorgeous?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:33:49.88,1:33:53.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我买给我老婆的  是两门的  我爱死它了\N{\fs16\fsp0}I bought it for my wife. It's a coupe. I love that car.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:33:55.89,1:33:58.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我怎么跟你说的  我确实跟你说过的\N{\fs16\fsp0}What did I tell you? I talked to you before, didn't I?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:33:58.93,1:34:00.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你不了解情况吗\N{\fs16\fsp0}Didn't I say what was going on?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:00.39,1:34:02.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我没告诉你暂时不要买东西吗\N{\fs16\fsp0}Didn't I say not to go buy anything for a while?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:02.66,1:34:05.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 竟然买辆新车  - 是我妈送的\N{\fs16\fsp0}- The fucking car? - It's a wedding gift from my mother.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:05.83,1:34:07.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,车主也是她  我才刚结婚呀\N{\fs16\fsp0}It's under her name. I just got married.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:08.13,1:34:10.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 我好爱那辆车  - 对不起  你等一下\N{\fs16\fsp0}- I love that car. - Excuse me, darling, for just a second.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:11.10,1:34:13.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 我刚结婚耶  - 你是不是疯了\N{\fs16\fsp0}- I just got married. - Are you nuts?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:13.54,1:34:16.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 你这么激动干什么  - 你是笨猪呀\N{\fs16\fsp0}- What are you getting excited for? - Are you stupid?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:16.51,1:34:19.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,外面有成千上万警察在注意我们\N{\fs16\fsp0}We got a million bulls out there. Everybody's watching us.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:19.25,1:34:21.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你居然弄了辆新车  还说我激动\N{\fs16\fsp0}And you get a fucking car. I'm excited?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:21.18,1:34:23.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那是我用我妈名字登记的  那是结婚礼物嘛\N{\fs16\fsp0}It's under my mother's name. It's a wedding gift.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:23.22,1:34:25.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不管是登记谁的名字  你是真笨还是假笨呀\N{\fs16\fsp0}I don't give a fuck. Are you stupid?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:25.75,1:34:27.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你没听见我说的吗  什么都不要买\N{\fs16\fsp0}Didn't you hear what I said? Don't buy anything.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:27.92,1:34:31.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,特别是大东西  你没听见我这么说的吗\N{\fs16\fsp0}Don't get anything. Nothing big. What's the matter with you?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:31.72,1:34:33.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你到底是怎么搞的\N{\fs16\fsp0}What are you getting excited for?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:33.23,1:34:36.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为你会连累我们被捕  你白痴啊\N{\fs16\fsp0}Because you're going to get us all fucking pinched. What are you, stupid?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:34:36.76,1:34:39.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 你是怎么搞的  - 对不起\N{\fs16\fsp0}- What's the matter with you? - I apologize.{\r}
