Dialogue: 0,2:05:59.47,2:06:03.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在我要好好计划保住性命  尽快把货脱手\N{\fs16\fsp0}Now my plan was to stay alive long enough to sell off the dope...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:06:03.41,2:06:07.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,躲起来一阵子  让我慢慢把所有事情摆平\N{\fs16\fsp0}the cops never found, then disappear until I can get things straightened out.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:06:09.61,2:06:10.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,操\N{\fs16\fsp0}Fuck!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:06:10.78,2:06:14.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 凯伦  我藏起来的那批货呢  - 我冲下马桶了\N{\fs16\fsp0}- Where's the stuff I left, Karen? - I flushed it down the toilet.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:06:16.25,2:06:17.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你干了什么\N{\fs16\fsp0}You what?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:06:17.89,2:06:20.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我该怎么办  到处都是条子\N{\fs16\fsp0}What was I supposed to do? They were all over the house.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:06:20.59,2:06:24.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那是我们的全部财产  价值6万块  我需要那些钱\N{\fs16\fsp0}That was worth $60,000! I need that money! That's all we got!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:06:24.83,2:06:27.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我能怎么办  他们有搜查令\N{\fs16\fsp0}What was I supposed to do? They had a search warrant!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:06:27.67,2:06:32.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你为什么要这么做  我们只有那些钱\N{\fs16\fsp0}That's all the money we had! I was depending on that! Why did you do that?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:06:32.64,2:06:35.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我没办法  他们一定会找到的\N{\fs16\fsp0}I had to. They were going to find it!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:06:35.61,2:06:39.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 他们绝不会找到的  - 我敢发誓\N{\fs16\fsp0}- They would have never found it! - They would have, I swear to you!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:06:41.01,2:06:42.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们一定会找到的\N{\fs16\fsp0}They would've found it!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:06:44.12,2:06:45.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你为什么要这样做\N{\fs16\fsp0}Why did you do that?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:06:45.72,2:06:49.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 他们一定会找到的  - 你为什么要这样做\N{\fs16\fsp0}- They would have found it. - Why did you do that, Karen?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:06:50.52,2:06:52.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我的天呀\N{\fs16\fsp0}Oh, my God!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:06:52.92,2:06:55.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 我是迫不得已  - 我的天呀\N{\fs16\fsp0}- I had to do it. - Oh, my God.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:07:32.00,2:07:33.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,保利  我真的很抱歉\N{\fs16\fsp0}Paulie, I'm really sorry.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:07:36.60,2:07:39.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不知道该说什么才好  我知道我犯了严重的错误\N{\fs16\fsp0}I don't know what else to say. I know I fucked up.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:07:39.87,2:07:41.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你搞砸了\N{\fs16\fsp0}Yeah, you fucked up.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:07:44.88,2:07:46.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但我现在没事了\N{\fs16\fsp0}But I'm all right now.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:07:48.35,2:07:52.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你可以相信我  我拿我孩子做保证\N{\fs16\fsp0}I can be trusted now. I'm clean. On my kids, I'm clean.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:07:52.88,2:07:55.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你睁着眼对我说谎\N{\fs16\fsp0}You looked in my eyes and lied to me.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:07:56.39,2:07:58.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,把我当冤大头\N{\fs16\fsp0}You treated me like a fucking jerk.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:07:59.12,2:08:00.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,毫无分量\N{\fs16\fsp0}Like I was never nothing to you.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:08:00.79,2:08:03.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你警告过我们  所以我更不敢向你说实话了\N{\fs16\fsp0}After what you said, I couldn't come to you.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:08:04.80,2:08:07.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我从那时起到现在\N{\fs16\fsp0}You know, I was ashamed.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:08:10.20,2:08:12.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,都很惭愧\N{\fs16\fsp0}I'm ashamed now.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:08:15.51,2:08:17.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但是我已经走投无路了  保利\N{\fs16\fsp0}But I got nowhere else to go, Paulie.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:08:20.91,2:08:25.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我现在只有求你了  我真的需要你的帮助\N{\fs16\fsp0}You're all I've got. And I really need your help. I really do.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:08:31.42,2:08:32.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,拿着\N{\fs16\fsp0}Take this.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:08:47.54,2:08:49.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,从现在起我不认识你了\N{\fs16\fsp0}And now I've got to turn my back on you.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:09:00.08,2:09:01.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,三千两百块\N{\fs16\fsp0}$3,200.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:09:02.32,2:09:06.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一生替他做事  他就给了我三千两百块\N{\fs16\fsp0}That's what he gave me. $3,200 for a lifetime.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:09:07.22,2:09:09.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,连买棺材都不够\N{\fs16\fsp0}It wasn't even enough to pay for the coffin.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:09:09.66,2:09:11.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 我们得跑路了  - 我不想跑\N{\fs16\fsp0}- We got to get out. - I don't want to run.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:09:11.86,2:09:16.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,难道你要我放弃一切  找地方躲起来吗\N{\fs16\fsp0}I don't want to. Am I supposed to pick up and leave everything? Go hiding?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:09:16.67,2:09:19.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不要  那就是你所要的生活吗\N{\fs16\fsp0}I don't want to do that. Is that what you want?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:09:19.34,2:09:21.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们留在这里  我们就死定了\N{\fs16\fsp0}If we stay around here, we're dead.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:09:22.27,2:09:24.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,死定了  懂不懂\N{\fs16\fsp0}You got it? We're dead.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:09:24.74,2:09:25.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们说得没错\N{\fs16\fsp0}They're right.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:09:26.34,2:09:29.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你药嗑太多了  你已经完全神经过敏了\N{\fs16\fsp0}You took too much of that stuff. You're totally paranoid.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:09:32.95,2:09:34.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他还好吧  有没有找他麻烦\N{\fs16\fsp0}How's he doing? Busting his balls or what?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:09:34.89,2:09:35.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他还好\N{\fs16\fsp0}He's okay.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:09:37.09,2:09:38.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他把嗑药的毛病改掉了\N{\fs16\fsp0}They sobered him up.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:09:38.86,2:09:40.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那就好\N{\fs16\fsp0}Good. Very good. Glad to hear it.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:09:44.93,2:09:47.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他有没有告诉你  条子问了他一些什么样的问题\N{\fs16\fsp0}You know what kind of questions they're asking him?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:09:47.40,2:09:48.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,吉米  我不知道\N{\fs16\fsp0}Jimmy, I don't know.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:09:50.07,2:09:53.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我心情太乱了  我又没有钱\N{\fs16\fsp0}I got my mind on so many other things. I got no money...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:09:54.17,2:09:56.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,孩子们都已经会看报纸了\N{\fs16\fsp0}The girls are old enough to read the newspapers.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:09:56.94,2:09:58.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你回去叫他马上给我打电话\N{\fs16\fsp0}Tell him he's got to call me. Okay?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:09:59.84,2:10:03.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们要好好处理这件事  这是非常重要的\N{\fs16\fsp0}As soon as you talk to him, he's got to call me. It's important.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:10:03.81,2:10:07.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他不知道我来找你  他现在不是很正常\N{\fs16\fsp0}He doesn't know I came here to see you. It's like he's crazy.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:10:07.59,2:10:10.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 先拿去救急  有几千块钱  - 谢了  吉米\N{\fs16\fsp0}- Take this. It's a couple of thousands. - Thanks, Jimmy.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:10:10.89,2:10:12.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不要太担心好吗  一切都会过去的\N{\fs16\fsp0}Don't worry, everything will be all right.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:10:12.99,2:10:16.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我有一批很漂亮的迪奥女裙\N{\fs16\fsp0}I got some beautiful Dior dresses. You want to have them?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:10:16.56,2:10:18.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,去挑几件喜欢的吧\N{\fs16\fsp0}Pick out a few for yourself.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:10:19.23,2:10:20.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 挑给我妈妈  - 可以  没问题  随便挑\N{\fs16\fsp0}- For my mom. - Yeah, whatever.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:10:21.33,2:10:23.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不  不  是在转角仓库\N{\fs16\fsp0}No. It's over here. In the store on the corner.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:10:24.17,2:10:26.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,因为是赃物  我放在角落\N{\fs16\fsp0}It's swag, so I got it down on the corner.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:10:32.54,2:10:34.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,去吧  甜心  再见\N{\fs16\fsp0}Go ahead, sweetheart, I'll see you.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:10:34.48,2:10:36.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 谢谢  吉米  - 不用担心\N{\fs16\fsp0}- Thanks, Jimmy. - Don't worry.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:10:36.41,2:10:39.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 我知道  - 不要忘了  打电话给我\N{\fs16\fsp0}- I'll try. - Don't forget, he's got to call me.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:10:41.62,2:10:43.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 这边吗  - 一直走\N{\fs16\fsp0}- Over here? - Right down there.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:10:58.87,2:11:00.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一直走  在转角\N{\fs16\fsp0}It's over there, on the corner.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:11:01.21,2:11:02.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就在那里\N{\fs16\fsp0}Right there.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:11:36.67,2:11:38.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不是  去呀  就在里面\N{\fs16\fsp0}No, go ahead. It's right in there.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:11:38.98,2:11:41.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不用了  吉米  我在赶时间\N{\fs16\fsp0}No, Jimmy. I'm in a hurry!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:11:41.41,2:11:44.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我妈在看孩子  我得回去\N{\fs16\fsp0}My mom's watching the kids! I got to get home!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:11:44.38,2:11:45.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,以后再来拿\N{\fs16\fsp0}I'll come back later!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:12:08.34,2:12:09.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,凯伦\N{\fs16\fsp0}Karen!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:12:14.48,2:12:15.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,发生什么事了\N{\fs16\fsp0}What happened?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:12:16.91,2:12:17.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没事\N{\fs16\fsp0}Nothing.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:12:18.55,2:12:20.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 到底什么事  - 我只是突然怕起来了\N{\fs16\fsp0}- What happened? - I just got scared.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:12:23.95,2:12:25.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,车钥匙拿了没有\N{\fs16\fsp0}Got the keys?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:12:26.86,2:12:30.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 到底什么事  - 我只是害怕起来了\N{\fs16\fsp0}- What happened, Karen? - I just got scared. It's okay.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:12:30.66,2:12:32.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 没事吧  - 现在没事了\N{\fs16\fsp0}- Are you all right? - Yeah.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:12:39.17,2:12:43.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果你是黑手党员  你永远不会知道几时会被杀\N{\fs16\fsp0}If you're part of a crew, nobody ever tells you they're going to kill you.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:12:44.28,2:12:46.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没人会事先通知你的\N{\fs16\fsp0}It doesn't happen that way.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:12:46.21,2:12:49.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也不像电影里先大吵大骂\N{\fs16\fsp0}There aren't any arguments or curses like in the movies.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:12:49.81,2:12:53.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,来杀你的人面带笑容  像是你很亲近的朋友\N{\fs16\fsp0}Your murderers come with smiles. They come as your friends.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:12:54.05,2:12:56.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们一直很关心你\N{\fs16\fsp0}People who cared for you all your life.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:12:56.25,2:13:00.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,在你有困难时  他们总会来帮助你\N{\fs16\fsp0}They always seem to come when you're weakest and most in need of their help.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:13:00.99,2:13:04.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,所以我跟吉米约好在人多的地方见面\N{\fs16\fsp0}So I met Jimmy in a crowded place we both knew.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:13:04.60,2:13:08.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我早到了15分钟  可吉米已经比我先到了\N{\fs16\fsp0}I got there 15 minutes early, and Jimmy was already there.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:13:09.03,2:13:13.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他占了靠窗的雅座  凡是来餐厅的人  他都看得见\N{\fs16\fsp0}He took the booth near the window so he could see everyone who drove up.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:13:13.77,2:13:16.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他要确认我没有被跟踪\N{\fs16\fsp0}He wanted to make sure I wasn't tailed.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:13:16.57,2:13:19.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他很紧张  什么也没吃\N{\fs16\fsp0}He was jumpy. He hadn't touched a thing.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:13:20.48,2:13:23.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,表面看来一点也没事\N{\fs16\fsp0}On the surface, everything was supposed to be fine.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:13:23.68,2:13:26.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们应该是要商量我的案子\N{\fs16\fsp0}We were supposed to be discussing my case.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:13:26.18,2:13:31.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,但我可以感觉到吉米在试探我是否会为了救自己而出卖他\N{\fs16\fsp0}But I had a feeling Jimmy was trying to sense if I'd rat on him to save my neck.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:13:32.79,2:13:36.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我一直提醒你  不要在电话上谈事情\N{\fs16\fsp0}I been telling you your whole life, don't talk on the phone.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:13:36.73,2:13:38.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在你明白了\N{\fs16\fsp0}Now you understand?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:13:41.17,2:13:44.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我想你胜诉的机会很大  一切会没问题的\N{\fs16\fsp0}It's going to be okay. You got a good chance to beat the case.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:13:47.67,2:13:51.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那个小子  你知道我是在说谁吧\N{\fs16\fsp0}You know that kid from the city we were talking about? You know?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:13:54.35,2:13:58.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那是个告密者  他一被捕就把所有的人都招供出来了\N{\fs16\fsp0}The kid turned out to be a rat. As soon as he got pinched, he ratted on everybody.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:14:01.35,2:14:03.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我知道他现在躲在哪里\N{\fs16\fsp0}I know where he is. He's hiding now.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:14:05.22,2:14:06.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,懂不懂我说的\N{\fs16\fsp0}Know what I'm saying?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:14:11.53,2:14:14.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你想你能和安东尼一方面度假  一方面把他解决掉吗\N{\fs16\fsp0}Would you have a problem going with Anthony to take care of that?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:14:17.80,2:14:18.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没问题\N{\fs16\fsp0}No, not at all.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:14:20.67,2:14:22.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,这样他们就没证人了\N{\fs16\fsp0}That way they got nothing.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:14:31.12,2:14:33.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,吉米从来没有叫我替他除掉任何人\N{\fs16\fsp0}Jimmy had never asked me to whack somebody before.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:14:34.32,2:14:37.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在他叫我和安东尼一起到佛罗里达去为他杀人\N{\fs16\fsp0}But now he's asking me to go to Florida and do a hit with Anthony.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:14:45.53,2:14:48.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,那时候我就知道  如果我去了佛州  我不会活着回来\N{\fs16\fsp0}That's when I knew I would never have come back from Florida alive.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:15:03.65,2:15:06.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不论你要把我们搬去哪里  我说过\N{\fs16\fsp0}Whenever you move me, I asked once and I'll tell you again...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:15:06.72,2:15:08.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不去寒冷的地方\N{\fs16\fsp0}I don't want to go any place cold.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:15:09.55,2:15:11.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你并没有选择余地\N{\fs16\fsp0}You don't have a choice in that matter.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:15:12.12,2:15:14.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,到底是谁管这个\N{\fs16\fsp0}Come on. Whoever fucking controls it...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:15:15.46,2:15:18.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,帮个忙  只要不是寒冷地方就行\N{\fs16\fsp0}just no place cold. Do that for me. I'm trying to...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:15:18.26,2:15:19.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他有气管炎\N{\fs16\fsp0}He's bronchial, that's why.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:15:20.16,2:15:22.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果检查后他真有气管炎  我们会列入考虑因素\N{\fs16\fsp0}If he's legitimately bronchial, we'll consider that.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:15:22.90,2:15:25.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我希望去不冷的地方\N{\fs16\fsp0}I'd like to go someplace not cold.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:15:25.27,2:15:29.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我能问一些问题吗  我父母会怎么样\N{\fs16\fsp0}Can I ask you some questions? What about my parents?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:15:30.11,2:15:31.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们怎么啦\N{\fs16\fsp0}What about them?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:15:31.28,2:15:33.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我能不能见他们  跟他们通消息\N{\fs16\fsp0}Am I going to see them? Am I going to talk to them?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:15:35.01,2:15:37.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,怎么跟他们联络\N{\fs16\fsp0}Don't I have some kind of contact with them?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:15:38.08,2:15:39.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不能\N{\fs16\fsp0}No.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:15:40.25,2:15:43.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,等一等  你是说\N{\fs16\fsp0}Wait a minute. Wait a minute. You mean to tell me that...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:15:43.95,2:15:47.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,就算我父母生病了  我也不能去看他们吗\N{\fs16\fsp0}God forbid something happens to my parents, they get sick, I can't see them?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:15:48.16,2:15:51.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也许可以特别安排  如果他们病了\N{\fs16\fsp0}Maybe something can be worked out if they're sick...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:15:51.63,2:15:53.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,情形特殊的话\N{\fs16\fsp0}if there's extraordinary circumstances...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:15:53.96,2:15:56.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不能这样做  亨利\N{\fs16\fsp0}I can't do this. I can't do this, Henry.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:15:57.94,2:15:59.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我不能留下我父母不管\N{\fs16\fsp0}I can't leave my parents.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:16:00.94,2:16:03.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,抱歉  凯伦  我跟你说了\N{\fs16\fsp0}Excuse me, Karen, I told you before.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:16:04.41,2:16:07.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,除非你跟孩子们和我在一起  我不会同意这个证人保护行动\N{\fs16\fsp0}I'm not going to do this unless you and the kids come with me.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:16:09.75,2:16:11.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我没有办法一个人捱过这些\N{\fs16\fsp0}I can't do it without you.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:16:11.85,2:16:15.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你要怎么做就怎么做  可是  就这样\N{\fs16\fsp0}So, you do whatever, but... that's it.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:16:17.45,2:16:19.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 你们需要亨利  并不需要我  对不对  - 没错\N{\fs16\fsp0}- You need Henry, not me, right? - That's right.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:16:20.36,2:16:22.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,老实说  我并不在乎你去不去\N{\fs16\fsp0}Frankly, I don't care whether you go or not.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:16:23.09,2:16:26.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如果能使他成为一个快乐而有用的证人  我希望你去\N{\fs16\fsp0}If it'll make him a better witness, I'd like you to be with him.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:16:26.53,2:16:28.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们要的是亨利  不是我\N{\fs16\fsp0}They want Henry, not me.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:16:28.40,2:16:31.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,亨利会受到保护  他们动不了他\N{\fs16\fsp0}Henry'll be in the protection program. They can't get to him.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:16:32.40,2:16:35.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,他们只能从你跟孩子身上动手来伤害亨利\N{\fs16\fsp0}They can only get to him by getting to you or your kids.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:16:36.01,2:16:38.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,假如他参与这次行动  你的处境就很危险\N{\fs16\fsp0}If he goes into the program, you're in danger...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:16:38.58,2:16:41.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 我什么也不知道呀  - 不要给我\N{\fs16\fsp0}- I don't know anything. - Don't give me...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:16:41.18,2:16:42.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,天真无邪那一套\N{\fs16\fsp0}the babe-in-the-woods routine.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:16:42.71,2:16:47.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我听过那些电话录音  你在电话中大谈白粉\N{\fs16\fsp0}I've listened to those wiretaps, and I've heard you talk about cocaine.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:16:47.45,2:16:50.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你跟亨利一通电话接着一通\N{\fs16\fsp0}Conversation after conversation you talked to Henry on the phone.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:16:55.93,2:16:57.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不管他是进监牢\N{\fs16\fsp0}It doesn't matter. Whether he goes to jail...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:16:58.13,2:17:01.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,还是胜诉了  他都一样是没命\N{\fs16\fsp0}or stays on the streets and beats the case, he's a dead man.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:17:02.17,2:17:03.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们心里都很清楚\N{\fs16\fsp0}He knows it and you know it.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:17:05.54,2:17:07.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们的孩子怎么办  他们要上学呀\N{\fs16\fsp0}What about the kids and school?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:17:07.34,2:17:09.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,总不能把他们留下\N{\fs16\fsp0}Will they get left back? I mean, what goes on?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:17:10.01,2:17:12.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你们为什么不到华尔街去抓那些真正的坏人\N{\fs16\fsp0}Go to Wall Street and get real crooks.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:17:12.88,2:17:15.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,卖西装给你们的人  真有幽默感\N{\fs16\fsp0}Whoever sold you those suits had a sense of humor.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:17:15.61,2:17:18.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,归根结底  和我们配合才是唯一救你们的方法\N{\fs16\fsp0}What it comes down to is we're your only salvation.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:17:19.15,2:17:22.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们会保障你们的生命  也会不让他去坐牢\N{\fs16\fsp0}We'll save your life and his life, and we'll keep you out of jail.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:17:26.82,2:17:29.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,今天早上你曾把你的背景向陪审团说明\N{\fs16\fsp0}This morning you told the jury about your background.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:17:29.83,2:17:31.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,要从人群中消失并不是一件困难的事\N{\fs16\fsp0}It was easy for us to disappear.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:17:32.00,2:17:34.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,房子是岳母的名字\N{\fs16\fsp0}My house was in my mother-in-law's name.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:17:34.30,2:17:36.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,车是我老婆的名字\N{\fs16\fsp0}My cars were registered to my wife.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:17:36.43,2:17:39.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,社会福利卡以及驾照都是假的\N{\fs16\fsp0}My Social Security cards and driver's licenses were phonies.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:17:40.04,2:17:42.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,没投过票  没缴过税\N{\fs16\fsp0}I never voted or paid taxes.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:17:42.97,2:17:47.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,唯一能表示有我这个人存在的是出生证明和犯罪记录\N{\fs16\fsp0}My birth certificate and arrest sheet was all you'd ever have to know I was alive.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:17:47.61,2:17:50.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 那个人在法庭内吗  - 是的\N{\fs16\fsp0}- Do you see him here in this courtroom? - Yes.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:17:50.58,2:17:52.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你能为陪审团将他指证出来吗\N{\fs16\fsp0}Will you please point him out for the jury?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:17:55.59,2:18:00.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,法官大人  请记录下来  希尔先生已正式指证了詹姆斯·康威\N{\fs16\fsp0}Let the record reflect that Mr. Hill identified the defendant, James Conway.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:18:01.33,2:18:04.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你也认识一位叫保罗·西席罗的人\N{\fs16\fsp0}Do you also know a man named Paul Cicero?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:18:04.76,2:18:06.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 那个人在这个法庭内吗  - 是的\N{\fs16\fsp0}- Do you see him in the courtroom? - Yes.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:18:07.33,2:18:09.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,你能为陪审团将他指证出来吗\N{\fs16\fsp0}Can you point him out for the jury?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:18:11.20,2:18:15.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,法官大人  请记录下希尔先生已指证了保罗·西席罗\N{\fs16\fsp0}Let the record reflect that Mr. Hill identified the defendant, Paul Cicero.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:18:16.64,2:18:18.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,法官大人  我这里有一份文件\N{\fs16\fsp0}Your Honor, I have a document...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:18:18.51,2:18:20.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,对我来说  最困难的就是从那种生活方式中走出来\N{\fs16\fsp0}The hardest thing was leaving the life.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:18:21.68,2:18:23.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我还是喜爱那种生活\N{\fs16\fsp0}I still love the life.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:18:23.61,2:18:25.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们像电影明星一样被礼遇\N{\fs16\fsp0}We were treated like movie stars with muscle.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:18:25.88,2:18:27.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只要开口  要什么有什么\N{\fs16\fsp0}We had it all, just for the asking.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:18:28.12,2:18:31.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,老婆  母亲  孩子  人人都能享受\N{\fs16\fsp0}Our wives, mothers, kids, everybody rode along.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:18:31.76,2:18:34.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一包纸袋的珠宝藏在厨房\N{\fs16\fsp0}I had paper bags filled with jewelry stashed in the kitchen.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:18:35.09,2:18:37.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一缸白粉就放在床边\N{\fs16\fsp0}I had a sugar bowl full of coke next to the bed.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:18:37.53,2:18:41.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,称为鼠辈  是因为老鼠为了求生存  什么事都会做\N{\fs16\fsp0}People call them rats because rats do anything to survive. Isn't that right?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:18:41.50,2:18:43.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 抗议  - 抗议成立\N{\fs16\fsp0}- Objection! - Objection sustained.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:18:43.70,2:18:46.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,- 至于老鼠我就不知道了  - 你太了解了\N{\fs16\fsp0}- I know nothing about being a rat. - You know everything about it.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:18:49.11,2:18:51.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,只要一通电话  什么都有\N{\fs16\fsp0}Anything I wanted was a phone call away.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:18:51.78,2:18:55.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,免费的汽车  城里所有的黑帮分子玩乐的地方都能自由进出\N{\fs16\fsp0}Free cars. Keys to a dozen hideout flats all over the city.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:18:55.38,2:18:57.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,一个周末可以下注两三万\N{\fs16\fsp0}I'd bet $20,000, $30,000 over a weekend...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:18:58.05,2:19:02.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,也可以一周内把赢的钱全花光  有时候也借高利贷来还赌债\N{\fs16\fsp0}then blow the winnings in a week or go to the sharks to pay the bookies.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:19:02.39,2:19:03.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,不过一点关系都没有\N{\fs16\fsp0}It didn't matter.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:19:04.15,2:19:09.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,钱花光了  我只要出去多抢一点就行了\N{\fs16\fsp0}It didn't mean anything. When I was broke I would go out and rob some more.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:19:09.43,2:19:10.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我们控制一切\N{\fs16\fsp0}We ran everything.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:19:11.36,2:19:15.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,收买条子  收买律师  甚至收买法官\N{\fs16\fsp0}We paid off cops. We paid off lawyers. We paid off judges.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:19:15.90,2:19:19.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,每个人都受贿  只要我们肯出钱\N{\fs16\fsp0}Everybody had their hands out. Everything was for the taking.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:19:21.44,2:19:22.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,现在都结束了\N{\fs16\fsp0}And now it's all over.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:19:23.87,2:19:25.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,难就难在这里\N{\fs16\fsp0}That's the hardest part.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:19:26.34,2:19:27.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,如今一切都不同了\N{\fs16\fsp0}Today everything is different.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:19:28.11,2:19:32.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我得像其他人一样等排班\N{\fs16\fsp0}There's no action. I have to wait around like everyone else.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:19:32.68,2:19:34.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,连像样的菜都吃不到\N{\fs16\fsp0}Can't even get decent food.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:19:35.22,2:19:38.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我搬来以后曾点过意大利面  加意大利蕃茄配料\N{\fs16\fsp0}After I got here I ordered spaghetti with marinara sauce...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:19:38.52,2:19:40.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,结果上的是鸡蛋面加蕃茄酱\N{\fs16\fsp0}and I got egg noodles and ketchup.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:19:41.19,2:19:42.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,我成为了无名小卒淡泊一生\N{\fs16\fsp0}I'm an average nobody.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:19:44.06,2:19:46.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,下半辈子得过得像个可怜虫\N{\fs16\fsp0}I get to live the rest of my life like a schnook.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,2:19:57.84,2:20:06.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,亨利·希尔目前仍在接受证人保护行动\N他于1987年在西雅图以贩毒罪名被捕\N但得到缓刑五年  此后不曾再犯罪
Dialogue: 0,2:20:07.38,2:20:13.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,1989年  亨利与凯伦在婚后25年正式离婚
Dialogue: 0,2:20:15.12,2:20:21.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,保罗·西席罗因呼吸道问题1988年死于监狱  享年73岁
Dialogue: 0,2:20:23.91,2:20:32.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,吉米·康威目前仍在纽约州监狱以谋杀的罪名服刑\N他必须等到2004年  他78岁时才能获得假释


